        public static User getUserById(int userId)
                        throws VivialConnectException
        Search for a User by its ID using the API.

        If the User is not found, a VivialConnectException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        userId - the id of the user to look up
        Returns:
        the User that was found given the id
        Throws:
        VivialConnectException - if there is an API-level error
        See Also:

      • getUsers

        public static List<User> getUsers()
                           throws VivialConnectException
        Gets all users for this Account using the API.

        If no User were found for this Account, the method will return an empty List

        Returns:
        a list of users
        Throws:
        VivialConnectException - if there is an API-level error
        See Also:
        getUserById(int), getUsers(Map)

      • getUsers

        public static List<User> getUsers(Map<String,String> queryParams)
                           throws VivialConnectException
        Search and filter every user for this Account using the API.

        If no User were found for this Account, the method will return an empty List.

        Parameters:
        queryParams - a map of String key-value pairs used to filter results, possible values are:

        page – Page number within the returned list of associated phone numbers. Default value: 1.

        limit – Number of results to return per page. Default value: 50. Maximum value: 150. order – Sort field and direction formatted like: [field]+[direction] where direction is one of ‘asc’ or ‘desc’. Default value: ‘id+asc’.

        Returns:
        a list of users
        Throws:
        VivialConnectException - if there is an API-level error
        See Also:
        getUsers(), getUserById(int)

      • delete

        public boolean delete()
               throws VivialConnectException
        Deletes this user from the database, dissociating it from the account.

        If the user you're trying to delete does not exist, a VivialConnectException holding a 404 response code will be thrown.

        Returns:
        a boolean value, indicating whether the user was deleted or not
        Throws:
        VivialConnectException - if there is an API-level error
